    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - LIGHT SYSTEMS - DESCRIPTION - Cab And Trailer
        Lights Switch
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cab And Trailer Lights Switch</title>
        <para>The cab and trailer lights switch is a switch that is used to flash (momentarily turn off) the tractor and
            trailer clearance and tail lights. Thus the truck operator can thank the driver of the vehicle he has just
            passed for flashing his headlights, signaling that it is safe to merge back into the driving lane.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
